Virtual inheritance - one subobject of Base class object

How to get one subobject of Base class object:
     Virtual inheritance 
	1) 	ScavTrap Virtual inherit ClapTrap ;
	2)	FragTrap  Virtual inherit ClapTrap;
	3)   DiamondTrap Virtual inherit ScavTrap and FragTrap;

This ensures that DiamondTrap has only one instance of ClapTrap, regardless of 
the multiple inheritance paths. 
	
This is achieved by the virtual base class mechanism,  which shares a single ClapTrap subobject 
among all the derived classes.

Understanding memory layout with and without Virtual inheritance:

Without  Virtual Inheritance:
	The object inheriting without virtual from parent, in addition to their own member attributes, they 
	maintains their own independent 'Parent' object instance portion

With Virtual inheritance:
		They will include space for their own members and pointers or mechanisms to access the 
		shared 'Parent' object instance, but not an actual Parent object of their own.

